I think this is an asynchronous problem : when Angular tries to display the data, it is still `undefined`, because your `getJSON()` function is asynchronous and `this.pizza` is not initialized yet.

First, try to change your function in your service :

```typescript
async getPizzaByNumber(number) { // Add async here
    console.log(&quot;getPizzaByNumber&quot;, number);
    const res = await this.getJSON(); // Add await here
    // Use await/async or .then() instead of subscribe for promises
    if (!res) return;
    this.pizza = res.find((el) =&gt; el.number == number); // Better than a forEach loop
    if (pizza) {
      console.log(&quot;Found Pizza: &quot;, this.pizza);
    }
  }
}
```
In show-order.ts :
```typescript
async getClickedPizza(pizza, userID, orderID, pizzaindex){ // Add async here
    console.log(&quot;userID&quot;, userID, &quot;orderID&quot;, orderID, &quot;pizzaindex&quot;, pizzaindex)
    this.OrderService.userID = userID;
    this.OrderService.orderID = orderID,
    this.OrderService.pizzaindex = pizzaindex;
    await this.OrderService.getPizzaByNumber(pizza.number); // Add await here
    this.NavController.navigateBack(&#39;extras&#39;);
  }
}
```

Then your error should disappear.

